VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> FEDU - Unidirectional Differential Electron Flux 2-60 MeV (time series)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: FPSA: Spin-Averaged Differential Proton Flux 20-120 MeV (spectrograms)
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Dimension 1 corresponds to 8 proton energy bins.

The centers of the proton energy bins.  The Value Uncertainty contains the plus/minus range for each bin.
The (Van Allen-Baker bowtie) plus/minus width of each energy bin from the center of the bin.
The efficiencies for the proton energy bins.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Dimension 1 corresponds to 8 proton energy bins.  Dimension 2 holds 36 sectors.

The (Van Allen-Baker bowtie) plus/minus width of each energy bin from the center of the bin.
The efficiencies for the proton energy bins.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The center of the sector in which the instrument is pointing.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: There are 36 sectors per spin of the satellite.  This is the center of each sector in degrees.  The Value Uncertainty contains the plus/minus range (of 5 degrees).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The plus/minus range from the center of each sector.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Each sector covers 10 degrees.  The range from the center is plus/minus 5 degrees.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The UTC time when the calibration set was applied.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The UTC time when the calibration set was applied during the day.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The number of times that the REPT calibration values changed during the day.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The values will be either zero, indicating the calibrations remained constant, or one, indicating the calibrations changed during the day.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: The data index (zero-based) corresponding to a calibration set.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The index, usually 0, of the first data that used the corresponding calibration set.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: A tag to identify the calibration set used during a day.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: This tag indicates the calibration set used to start the day.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: [Time-series] Position of the satellite in geographic coordinates
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Origin = Earths center of mass. X = Intersection of Greenwich meridian and geographic equator. Z = Geographic North Pole. Y = completes a right-handed Cartesian triad
0 denotes highest quality.
